CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 25, 1960, pg. A19, reads: "Alpha Wives - Chairmen of committees for the recent Alpha Wives' 'Fantasy of Roses' and luncheon-bridge at the Gateway Plaza was the above group. Seated (left to right): Mmes. Homer S. Brown, Eunice Washington, co-chairman of the affair; Easter Little, Miriam Fountain, president; Oteria Nickleson and Mary Gloster. Standing:  Mmes. Eleanor Jennings, who with Eunice Washington and Bobbie Miller sold the most tickets; Gladys McCullough, Cecile Springer, Palistine Zellars, Mary Hall Page and Alice Parr. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of wives of Alpha fraternity members seated from left: Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, Eunice Washington, Easter Little, Miriam Fountain, Oteria Nickleson, Mary Gloster; standing: Eleanor Jennings, Gladys McCullough, Cecile Springer, Palistine Zellars, Mary Hall Page, and Alice Parr, posed in Gateway Plaza
